39    /**
40    * JMSTaskManager instance that will create, manage and also destroy
41    * idle tasks created for it, for message receipt. This will also allow individual tasks to cache
42    * the Connection, Session or Consumer as necessary, considering the transactionality required and
43    * user preference.
44    * <p/>
45    * This also acts as the ExceptionListener for all JMS connections made on behalf of the adapter.
46    * Since the ExceptionListener is notified by a JMS provider on a "serious" error, we simply try
47    * to re-connect. Thus a connection failure for a single task, will re-initialize the state afresh
48    * for the transport adapter, by discarding all connections.
49    */
 
47.5% Uncovered Elements: 166 (316) Complexity: 120 Complexity Density: 0.66
